YESTERDAY was day 19 and once again, I couldn't wait to get onto the mat.  I absolutely love this 31 day challenge and I am looking forward to joining in the challenge around new year.  I am really curious to know what other uploads Adriene has on her site as I went from doing The Self Love Yoga to this revolution journey.

In the last 20 days, I didn't think I was making many steps when it comes to improving my health and wellbeing, but I am finally noticing the small changes that have come through with these challenges.  I am focused on my breathing, I am pushing myself to my limits and I am trying to improve my yoga journey by staying with this programme through the 30 minutes, and taking a new step by following Adriene.  I still don't have flexibility but I am not worried but at least I am finding time in my day to really focus on myself and don't let the outside world get in my way.

Yesterday, I could have given up because family came around and it is so easy to say "I won't do it, I will do it later", but I stuck to my guns and found the 30 minutes in the morning to make this happen.  I am always grateful at the end of each session that I took the time, to come to the mat, work within my limit and also push new boundaries because when the time is up, I am always in a good place and I look forward to continuing my day.
